    Outputs
        I:Ideal
    Description
        Text
          Given a set points $X$, it returns the defining ideal of $I(X)$
        Example
            S = QQ[x,y,z] 
            X = {point{1,1,0},point{0,1,1},point{1,2,-1}}
            I = idealOfProjectivePoints(X,S)
            I2 = hadamardPower(I,2)
            X2 = hadamardPower(X,2)
            I2 == idealOfProjectivePoints(X2,S)
